    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You're right @vvo, great point!\r\n\r\nHow about?\r\n\r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.analytics({\r\n    pushFunction: function(query, parameters, nbHits) {\r\n      // Do whatever you want - use API of your analytics services \r\n      // and we'll make sure they are pushed in the right time    \r\n      \r\n      // For example GA:\r\n\r\n      window.ga('set', 'page', '/search/query/?query = ' + query + '&params= ' + params + '&numberOfHits=' + nbHits);\r\n      window.ga('send', 'pageView');\r\n    }, \r\n    // other configs like delay etc...\r\n  })\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo we won't be responsible for maintaining 3rd parties APIs and we just make sure the data are pushed in the right time with correct data.\r\n\r\nLooks better?\r\n\r\ncc @bobylito @Shipow ",
