  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Having services already integrated would be great until certain time. I tend to agree on this with @vvo, as in long term it'd be pain to maintain.\r\nAnd we have to remember power-users who already have their GA configured and when we provide them prepared service, it might have some limitations. For example now we push GA pageView with URL `/search/query/?query=' + query...` but a lot of customers can have configured GA to handle search with URL `/?q=' + query...`. So using widget with already integrated services might cause them issues and additional effort in the implementation unless we give them all options as configurable (and I'm afraid we cannot handle all).\r\n\r\nFor me the best way is to expose them `pushFuction` as proposed and handle different services in guide/tutorial/documentation. And we won't be limited by integrated services and when somebody wants to use other one - feel free :)\r\n\r\nRight now we serialise parameters as we think is good. Not the best option :D But what we can do is to expose whole `helper` inside the `pushFunction` so power-users can get any data they want. Would it be a good idea?\r\n\r\nTimeout 3 seconds is default for now and is configurable. In the end, we can always reduce default value to 2 seconds or less?\r\nThe case when user do action before 3 seconds are handled by `click` and `beforeunload` event listeners. Do you think it's not enough?",
